{
  "texts": [
    "As I will explain, the elemental ethics mobilised by MOSACAT and the Council also raises deep questions over well-being and survival, questioning the prominence gained by concerns over hypothetical 'rogue' AI scenarios that could bring about human extinction.",
    "The rest of this article is structured as follows.",
    "First, I analyse the main concerns of research on AI ethics and sustainable AI and foreground some of their limitations.",
    "After that, I turn to environmental philosophy to unpack elemental thinking.",
    "I then describe my methodological choices and procedures (interviews, participatory methods and material-semiotic analysis) and introduce the two case studies at stake: a Google data centre project in Santiago and lithium extraction in the Atacama Desert."
  ]
}